{
  "text": "Cells were analyzed for apoptosis after visualization of nuclei morphology with fluorescent DNA-binding dye Hoechst 33342, as described previously [CITATION_1] . After treatment, cells were rinsed with PBS and incubated with 5 \u03bcg/ml Hoechst 33342 for 10 min. Nuclei were visualized at 400\u00d7 magnification using fluorescent microscopy at an excitation wavelength of 330-380 nm. Apoptotic nuclei of cells were assessed by counting the number of cells that displayed nuclear morphology changes, such as chromatin condensation and fragmentation.",
